                </div>
            </section>
            <section>
                <div class="card">
                    <h2> Methods </h2>
                    <div class="subcaption-edit">
                        <h2><em> We test the activation of the Csm6 proteins using the synthetic activators in the following table:  </em></h2>
                    <img src="https://2021.igem.org/wiki/images/a/af/T--UCSC--character_getting_sick.png"/>
                    </div>
                    <div class="subcaption-edit">
                        <h2><em> We use the following RNA targets for Csm6 that will serve as templates in qPCR and a TaqMan assay using digital PCR in order to measure level of activation: </em></h2>
                    <img src="https://2021.igem.org/wiki/images/a/af/T--UCSC--character_getting_sick.png"/>
                    <img src="https://2021.igem.org/wiki/images/a/af/T--UCSC--character_getting_sick.png"/>
                    </div>
                    <p> Typically, a TaqMan is used to quantify the presence or absence of a certain target sequence. The reaction uses a fluorescently labeled probe whose sequence matches to the target. The probe binds to the target sequence as well as forward and reverse primers. The primers allow Taq polymerase to start amplifying the target, but once it reaches the fluorophore on the end of the probe, Taq cuts the probe which causes it to fluoresce. Thus, fluorescence would indicate the presence of the target. </p>

                    <p> However, in our case we intend to use this method to quantify how much RNA is cut by Csm6. So we will incubate the Csm6 with the activators and target sequence, then add the products to the TaqMan assay in a digital PCR machine. If Csm6 was properly activated, then it should have destroyed the target sequence, preventing the primers and/or probes from attaching properly, leading to no fluorescence. Thus if there is no fluorescence, Csm6 was activated; if there is fluorescence, Csm6 did not work.  </p>
                    <div class="subcaption-edit">
                        <h2><em> Caption for figure below this ----> </em></h2>
                    <img src="https://2021.igem.org/wiki/images/a/af/T--UCSC--character_getting_sick.png"/>
                    </div>
            </section>
